Poland’s Zloty Slides Second Day Against Euro; Forint Weakens

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-09-09T06:54:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/poland-s-zloty-slides-second-day-against-euro-forint-weakens.html
The Polish zloty and  Hungary ’s
forint weakened for a second day against the euro.  The zloty depreciated 0.6 percent to 4.2795, the lowest
intraday level since Nov. 4, 2009, at 8:51 a.m. in Warsaw. The
forint lost 0.1 percent to 277.3 per euro.  -Editors: Stephen Kirkland, Ana Monteiro  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest 
 agergely@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  